**What MinRes can offer you**

-   Step into a key leadership role with real influence over production
    outcomes, safety performance and day to day decision making on site.

-   We invest in your career, with a focus on leadership, upskilling,
    training and development.

-   Access to a range of benefits to look after the important things in
    life -- family, health, fun and your future.

** **

**About the role**

Reporting to the Mining Superintendent, this role will be responsible
for providing high quality guidance and leadership to the mining teams,
through mentoring, coaching and for ensuring a safe work environment.
This role will be an 2/1 FIFO roster to Weipa Project from Brisbane or
Cairns.

 

**Key Responsibilities**

-   Organising and scheduling the mining crew to meet daily production
    targets

-   Management of production and mechanical break-down issues

-   Accountability for providing comprehensive reporting to the
    management team on production achievements, challenges and issues

-   Providing effective guidance, coaching and mentoring to site
    personnel

-   Maintaining and fostering a working environment which prompts safety
    in all that we do, whilst also providing outstanding service

-   Development of working relationships with key stakeholders on site

-   Work closely with maintenance to minimise downtime and ensure fast
    turnaround on breakdowns

-   Directly monitor fleet productivity in real time, taking immediate
    corrective action when output drops below plan targets

-   Aggressively identify and remove bottlenecks in haulage, loading,
    and dumping operations to maximise operating time

 

**What you will bring to the team**

-   Minimum 5 years' experience working within a Mining and Production
    Environment

-   Previous experience working in mining and working towards production
    targets

-   Previous experience successfully leading a team

-   Demonstrated strong problem solving, lateral thinking and analytical
    skills

-   Excellent time management and daily routine rituals

-   Strong communication skills, written and verbal with an ability to
    import knowledge, coach and mentor others

 

**About CSI Mining Services**

CSI, a wholly owned subsidiary of Mineral Resources (MinRes), is one of
Australia's largest mining services contractors. CSI provides
world-class tailored crushing, screening and processing solutions and
mining services for some of the world's largest mining companies. 

Service offerings include design, manufacture, commissioning and on-site
operation and maintenance of plant facilities, as well as specialised
mine services such as mine planning, drill and blast, load and haul,
plant and equipment hire and maintenance, tails recovery, aggregate
crushing and mine design, as well as engineering and construction. 

Be part of our exciting next chapter. 
